T--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr> Okay, so I've finnaly finished this quest, the first one to do so to my knowledge, so here you go, full spoiler on the Wizard only charm from LoY - Charm of the Combine. Hope this is the right forum.<br>
<br>
The Quest begins with Researcher Vexil (erudite) in the Gulf of Gunthak.<br>
<br>
** Note: Do not read any further if you wish to solve this quest no your own**<br>
------------------------------------------------------------<br>
<br>
He spawn in the ship washed ashore at : -721, -281. He does have a PH, which is the &quot;A vicious skeleton' sitting at that loc.<br>
<br>
Upon talk to Vexil he will tell you the story of the spires as we know them (the combine used them, etc). He says that him and his crew of adventurers were traveling to the different continents to study the spires when they were caught in a storm and their ship washed ashore here, now they are stranded. He asks if you are willing to pick up his research where he left off.<br>
<br>
Say &quot;I am willing&quot; and he will give you a 6 slot combineable bag (no drop). He will then tell you that he needs you to fill that bag with relics from the great spires. If you should ever happen to find all 5 of them then seal the bag with relics inside. Then seek out one who was Al'Kabors assistant. Vexil cannot remember his name and is not sure where he is currently residing, but he does remember him being a 'devious Gnome' (Terblyn Zelbus in the temple of sol ro of course).<br>
<br>
Now comes the frustrating part:<br>
<br>
Collecting the 'relics', What are you looking for is actually items that look like portal chips used for translocates called 'an arcane relic'. This part by far took me the longest in doing this quest. Let start with the easy ones first. (Note: all of the relics have the same name and look the same, even those they are lore and no drop you can collect the different ones no problem)<br>
<br>
Dreadlands relic: This is an easy on, it spawns in the Combine city ruins just south of the DL Port spires. You can find it on top of the pyramid at loc: +773, +9707. It looks like a small bag on the ground.<br>
<br>
North Karana relic: Another easy one, althought it took me a good 50 mins to find it the first time around. It's sitting on top of the Guard tower near the fire at: -4140, +1198. becareful if you are kos to qeynos guards, if you are put up invis before running up here.<br>
<br>
Greater Faydark relic: Another easy one buy hard to find due  to it not being directly near the spires. It's a littel past the felwithe entrance on the hill, it spawns on the ground as a small bag at: -1797, 2385<br>
<br>
Tox relic: This one was a pain in the ass, due to it being what I am guessing bugged. I found this by dumb luck and dumb luck only, this one kept me from advancing in the quest for over 2 weeks. I searched all over Tox and found nothing. Whenever I'd log on if nothing was going on i spent my time in tox looking for this, killing everything in the zone etc. Each time I ported in I would just do a shout out of habit if anyone had found something on the ground called 'an arcane relic'. Well one day I port in, do my shout and a level 2 newb/twink erudite responds back that he just piced one up. you know the kobolds and snakes that wander near the port in? welkl he was killing those, when one of the ones he killed died in a tree, i'm sure many of you have encountered this before. The mobs corpse gets stuck in the tree about head level to the PC, well he went to loot it and what does he see in the tree hovering on the side, a small brown bag! He showed me the rough area where he had gotten and I sat there and waited..and waited..and waited. AFter 5-6 hours it finnally spawned (lets hope all the relics dont take this long to respawn but I wouldn't be suprised). The loc of this relic is: -1118, -655, -42, note the height number in the loc, it spawns a littel ways up in a tree there, don't be an idiot and stare at the ground like me because you wont find anything.<br>
<br>
Finally the last relic, Nexus: Honestly I have no idea what the hell VI was thinking when they did this. This relic will either be a bitch to get for some of you or easy to get, depending on what you have done with your char. Just like the tox relic i discovered this one out of pure dumb luck. I can't tell you how much time i say in the nexus looking at the groundk and doing constant shouts asking if anyoen had picked up 'an arcane relic'. Well this past weekend my guild went to kill Greig Veneficus in Greig's end, while setting up for the pull a guildie ran up to greig after we killed his guards and right clicked him (you all know the one you kill is a merchant that sells nothing, right?) Well not axactly anymore. Turns out sometime (maybe in LoY patch?) they added an item to his sell table, the only item he sells, yup you guessed it, &quot;an arcane relic&quot;, 1100pp depending on your faction and charisma. I spent the rest of the day working my grieg faction up. Ti my luck the servers came down that night, so the next morning I was able to drag a group of guildies up to GE so we could fight up to griegs room and I could run inside and buy the relic real quick before being slaughtered by his guards. (I got it, but I still died rather quickly =p). I don't know how I would ever found this relic if my guildie hadn't clicked greig to see what he had, maybe there is a missing like somewhere? I tried asking terblyn all about it, he wouldn't say anything. None the less, this is where the nexus relic is.<br>
<br>
Once you get all 5 relics, place them in the bag and hit combine. You'll get a lore no drop bag (fits in other containers now) called &quot;sealed arcane pack&quot;. Take this to Terblyn Zelbus in the solro temple and hand it to him. He'll examine it and tell you that this bag contains the needed magic to allow him to create a working teleport spire of his own. All he needs now is the complete frame of a spire and he'll be able to use the relics to make it work. At this point he gives you 2 no drop items. A 'not to Vexil' and a 4 slot container called 'empty spire frame'. He says to take the note to Vexil as he'll know what to do, but be wanred that the ones who hold the pieces of the spire frame won't be willing to part with them.<br>
<br>
Now at this point I returned back to Gunthak, with 3 groups of 60-65's We all buffed and formed a raid no knowing what to expect when I would hand in the note to Vexil. I handed the note to Vexil and he told us that he has heard tales from other sailors of 'Spire Crafters' in these parts that roam the oceans. At this point a ranger in our raid saw 4 'Spire Crafter' show up on track to the NW. He led us to them, all 4 underwater close together at the gate in the water (the gate you cant get through), loc: +288, +639 yellow to 63 so I am guessing they 65. We got them pac'd and a monk was able to FD pull them one at a time, they were pretty easy for 3 groups but I could see us failing if 3 came. They hit for ~350-450, had approx 80khp each and had an ae mana drain spell (sorry I cant recall the name, it wasn't for much, maybe 300-300 a drain?) It hit me everytime, I was never able to resist. Each one dropped a piece of the spire frame, &quot;Spire frame top left&quot; &quot;Spre frame top right&quot; etc, all no drop..<br>
<br>
Combine the 4 in the &quot;empty spire frame&quot; and you receive &quot;intact spire frame&quot;.<br>
<br>
Take it back to Terblyn Zelbus, he says he will need to further his research before attempting to create his own spire, but for your work he rewards you with : Charm of the Combine.<br>
<br>
Item stats are as follows: <br>
<br>
Charm of the Combine <br>
Magic Lore No Drop <br>
Slot: Charm <br>
Required level of 50. <br>
Wt:0.1 Size: Small <br>
Class: Wiz <br>
Race: All <br>
<br>
Item Information: <br>
Improves as you memorize more translocate spells. <br>
<br>
**1-3 Translocate spells memmed** <br>
-No change <br>
<br>
**4 Translocate spells memmed** <br>
Charm of the Combine <br>
Magic Lore No Drop <br>
Slot: Charm <br>
Required level of 50. <br>
AC: 8 Sta: 8 Wis: 8 Int: 8 Mana: 50 HP: 50 <br>
Effect: Flowing Thought I <br>
Wt:0.1 Size: Small <br>
Class: Wiz <br>
Race: All <br>
<br>
**5 Translocate spells memmed** <br>
-No change <br>
<br>
**6 Translocate spells memmed** <br>
Charm of the Combine <br>
Magic Lore No Drop <br>
Slot: Charm <br>
Required level of 50. <br>
AC: 10 Sta: 10 Wis: 10 Int: 10 Mana: 75 HP: 75 <br>
Effect: Flowing Thought II <br>
Wt:0.1 Size: Small <br>
Class: Wiz <br>
Race: All <br>
<br>
**7 Translocate spells memmed** <br>
